🟢 Language ➡ C
🟢 Topic ➡ Variable 


📦 Variables in C (Quick Notes)
Variable = Named memory location for store data that can be modified during execution.
It allows you to store different types of data 

🛠️ Declaration
 👉 Declare before use with data type and name.
       int age;

🧬 Data Types
Basic: int, float, double, char
Derived: Arrays, Pointers, Structures, Unions, Enums


🚀 Initialization
Can be done during declaration:
    int age = 25;


🌐 Scope
Local: Inside functions → limited access
Global: Outside functions → accessible everywhere



✍️ Naming Rules
Start with letter or _
Use letters, digits, _ only
Case-sensitive


✅ Types of Variable
a.Local
b.Global
c.Static - intialized only once and preserve the value till the wnd of the program 
d.automatic 
e.external 


🧠 Memory Storage
Local → Stack
Global/Static/Dynamic → Heap or Data Segment

